    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-10T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-10T16:00:00-05:00" n="477"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d477">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">860F.01/7–1145: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harriman</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-11T00:00:00+03:00"
                            >July 11, 1945—midnight</date>.<lb/>[Received 6:40 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2525. From Klieforth’s July 6, 6 p.m. (sent Dept as 64). I gather that Czech Govt
                    has requested complete withdrawal of American troops from Czecho in advance of
                    complete withdrawal of Russians. I consider it would have an adverse effect on
                    our relations with Russia if we were to yield to this demand. Russians are
                    extremely sensitive to considerations of prestige and any move on our part which
                    is interpreted by them as a sign of weakness or vacillation with respect to any
                    one of their actions often lands reflection of their attitude in numbers of
                    other fields not immediately affected by action in question.</p>
                <p>Sent Dept 2525; rptd Praha 17.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Harriman</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
